This prof is so sweet! I found her class extremely interesting,, essentially you'll hate the christian church after. Go figure. As long as you watch the lectures and take good notes, you'll do well on quizzes. Her lectures/films add up to less than the 3h class time per week. Readings are reasonable for a uni level course. first off - do not take this course. I was told it is an easy/interesting elective but THAT IT NOT THE CASE ANYMORE. The workload is beyond unrealistic compared to all my other courses. I was forced to take my courses online due to COVID, and her course load is respective of that. There are 5, 10% quizzes and a 50% final exam, making it relatively easy to focus on the class.
Shelley is an amazing prof. I learned a lot from her class and would jump at the chance to take another one of her classes

This course was an Easy A. In regards to the Prof: she does come off harsh and her attempt at humour may be off putting to students, but I was throughly entertained! Definitely doable to get the grade you want if youre willing to put in the work. She gave us more work to do because of the online format during COVID, but honestly, just do it. I found that she sometimes had some very tricky and highly specific questions, but overall the concepts are simple and the course is so interesting that its worth it.

Although this class is typically seen as an easy A, professor rabinovitch goes out of her way to inconvenience students and make it as difficult as possible to succeed. She took this course way too seriously for a first-year introduction course. I think she realizes people take it as a bird course, so she is extra uptight/strict/authoritative. It is still easy, but she is not fun.

I really enjoyed the subject material and lectures. For an online class, I found her class very organized. She is such an interesting lecturer with such unique experiences and knowledge to share. Interesting content. Terribly grouchy prof.

She's not very professional and inconveniences her students through purchase of textbook and monotone lectures. For an elective course, it's not the worst choice, but you're better off taking a course in another faculty, where you might learn something useful for the same amount of effort.

She was an awesome Prof! The class itself was incredibly interesting but she made it a so much more interesting. I wish The class never ended. She was easy to talk to and understanding!

DO NOT take this as a 3hr lecture. no powerpoints, no brightspace, old-fashioned listen to her talk and take notes, thats it. not a bird course. lots of readings (2 chapters per week plus 5-10 definitions) with a lot of unnecessary content. knowledgable prof but the 3 hour lectures are tiresome when you aren't allowed electronics. midterm is 40% and final is 60% and each question is a percent of your grade. lots of content so not a super easy course.

Shelley's voice is very engaging in class. Her midterm is 40% and finals 60%. Finals are a bit tough therefore get ready. Technological devices are not allowed in her classes, neither does she post slides so you have to go to class in order to get notes

She seems to be unapproachable, however she is very kind and her lectures are interesting. She is funny and makes jokes which makes her lectures not feel so long. Midterms and quizzes are pretty easy, and you just need to show up to take good notes and you should be fine.

EASYY CLASS! She is a no no for electronics. Take notes by hand. i liked the course material so i could sit for 3 hours without loosing conscious, but it could be boring for a lot of students. Very interesting input, sadly there were too many people.

She's an amazing crazy prof that loves what she's teaching and does not take anyone's bs. No electronics so you have to write by hand, but its not bad at all. Shelley is probably one of my favourite professors. She doesn't allow technology AT ALL which is a great strategy to get a great mark. The midterm and test is all MC/TF and there are no assignments. best prof #1 luv her my goddess

despite what everyone says about witchcraft being an easy elective, it really isn't. complete waste of an elective and this prof is SO rude and honestly i don't know what i've even learned. no electronics allowed, no talking, no anything really .. worst first year class experience ever, she's a disaster so avoid the course and her

What an amazing prof!! Really enjoyed this as an elective, definitely take this class if  at all possible. Lectures were very interesting, the 3 hour lecture went by very quickly. Prof Shelley is extremely knowledgeable in what she teaches. Had one midterm and a final; both MC format. Very easy, interesting course!

This professor is amazing! I work full time and I am completing my BA part-time so good lectures are important. She is great! Don't mess with her when it comes to class rules though (no phones in class and no laptop)!  Multiple choice and TF for midterm ( got 80%).

The teach and the topic are both interesting and engaging. Very repetitive with her jokes.

This is one of the hardest elective I have ever had.. Multiple choice does not always mean easier.. especially when it comes to her exams the questions are SO specific. Not to mention I started studying weeks before the midterm and did all the readings but still only got a B..

No lectures online, so attend class as lectures are all you're going to get.  Amazing prof, only one midterm and an exam, some specific questions on the midterm that were barely mentioned... Some material from the textbook is important for the tests, so read.  Loved this class.

Im sorry but this class is not as easy as everyone portrays it to be. Multiple choice tests are really hard... you need to study and know SPECIFIC things. The multiple choice options are so tricky. She can be intimidating, I sometimes felt like she was unapproachable because if you didn't agree with her then she wouldn't like you. This course can have some seriously triggering material and she was good with trigger warnings but sometimes she wouldn't give one or didn't specify what could be triggering but she took criticism really well

Hilarious, engaging and inspiring. Strict ban on electronics in class. Clear on expectations. Isn't afraid to tell students to shut up during lectures. Good notes are necessary because any little detail can and will be tested on. Only a midterm and final. Both easy if you read your notes a few times but don't slack since you're only tested twice.

Her 3 hour lectures fly by, she really captures the students attention. She explains everything over and over again making it easy to study for. Straightforward class, but a lot of information to retain, do not skip any classes!

really an inspiration woman who tells it like it is. shes got spunk. shes very anti-technology and demands respect. lectures were always interesting and easy to follow. sometimes i wishes classes were a little longer because it felt like there was so much more to be discussed.

She has so many different stories to tell that make her lectures so interesting and she is very funny.  Doesn't feel like a 3 hour class at all.  Cellphones and laptops are not allowed while she's lecturing; she has called people out for that.  The only bad thing is that there's only a midterm and a final, so you can't mess up either of them.

Awesome class! Super interesting and she really keeps the students engaged during the lecture. She really knows her stuff and has a lot of experience in this field so it makes it even more interested! Do the readings and attend class and you should pass for sure!

Dr. Rabinovitch is hilarious! She has a super strict phone ban but otherwise, she's pretty awesome. Her stories and little side comments will make you laugh. Her midterm and exam questions are chosen fairly from her lectures, films, guest speakers. If you don't know what electives to take, choose this class or something else she teaches!

This prof is by far my favorite professor, and this class was one of the most interesting I have ever taken. She is so knowledgeable and you can really tell she loves to teach. Her lectures are so interesting and she has so much personal experience with her subject. I highly recommend this class to anyone! Take it! you will love it! shes hilarious

The lectures are very interesting and the teacher's crazy sense of humour and anecdotes make the class really fun! The title of the course may only imply witchcraft, but in class, so many subjects are discussed and it is simply fascinating!  Recommended 100%

She is a very funny prof, but loves to ramble.  She is really clear in what is important and not. Midterm and final are multiple choice, so it is very easy.  did not attend most lectures and still finished with an 80. Pretty interesting. Would recommend the class and the prof.

She will change your life. She is so entertaining and knows what she's talking about. Note: you only have two chances for marks (mid-term & exam) STUDY for these. This is not a bird course. If you don't study, you will pay. She is really funny. Can't use phones during her class. Attend class and do the readings (they are mandatory to passing).

By far the best prof I have had. Not only is she funny, but she relates course material to her own life and always has stories to share. She does not post slides online, nor does she use any electronics. And you will get kicked out if you use any sort of electronic in her class. Listen to her speak, take good notes, and there's your B+

I can't believe there are any bad reviews for this professors - easily one of the most enthusiastic, excited and involved professors I've ever had. Made me fall in love with the topic, and even declare it as a second major.  Truly a dedicated professor

Dr. Rabinovitch is just FANTASTIC. The course itself is fairly interesting and easy to do well in. Exams are multiple choice, and very straightforward. If you do your readings, pay attention during lectures  and take good notes- This class is an easy A+.

Excellent prof - a leader in her field. Course is well structured, lectures are fascinating, though a bit too personal at times for my taste. Still, a rewarding experience, no wonder it's such a popular course.

Very interested in the material, and the professor was nice; however, it was just so.... blah. She rambled on a lot of the time and somehow made me actually fall asleep in one of her lectures. Exams were VERY specific although multiple choice. It may have included one thing she said that one time in that one lecture.. very unimportant stuff.

Although very intimidating, LOVED her class. I loved the material so it was a very interesting course. The fact that the use of electronics is not permitted sucks, but other than that, I have no complaints!

Wonderful professor and a good & kind person.  It is not a 'hard' course, but you have to attend classes and do the reading to succeed (unless you're a really good guesser).  The lectures are interesting and well-organized.  She's approachable and very fair.

The class is a bird course if you attend every class and do the readings. Readings are a must if you want 90+. Prof Rabinovitch is an amazing prof and makes the lectures interesting. The workload is quite light and the exams are easy if you took good notes.

She is awesome and this class was very interesting! I would take it again in a heartbeat. Huge class size, over 400 people. You must write 2 exams, midterm and final, all multiple choice, and you have no essays or assignments which I liked. Go to class, pay attention, take decent notes, and you will do great.

Very interesting class! Professor is very knowledgeable and clearly loves what she does. Class is a breeze if you attend, take notes and do your readings. Questions are not nearly as random as some have said. I love that she calls out on students who are talking, very refreshing!

Love this professor! She is very knowledgeable about the subject and is very respectful. She is clear and concise in her lectures and gives you specific terms to focus on that usually end up on the exams. The exams are fair because she genuinely wants students to do well. If you attend all classes and read the textbook you will do fine!

I agree with a previous poster: this class is not as easy as it's made out to be. Not only does every mistake on the multiple choice midterm (40%) and final (60%) count for 1% of your final grade, the questions are random (kinda like trivia). Readings are a must!
Very interesting, I loved going to class. Knows what she's talking about, great lectures. No electronics (for the best).

This class isn't as easy as it's made out to be. But if you attend the lectures, take good notes (she doesn't allow computers or any electronics because she says its distracting, which is true), and read the books, you'll do very well. She tries to make you succeed but every mc mistake costs you 1%
Got a bad first impression, but she gets better! The course material is super interesting, the prof does not seem very enthusiastic about teaching and  was not very prepared. Marking is easy.
This course is overrated. Course material is in fact interesting, however, the way the professor "teaches" the material is horrible. Avoid the class if possible or take it with another professor.

Very interesting course but definitely something to boost your mark up.  Midterm and final were very easy, aside from a few questions from left field.  Prof is funny but quite crude, if that isn't your thing.  If you're looking for an easy 'bird' course, definitely recommend.

Easy A for sure! Only one midterm and one final I recommend taking this class with Rabinovitch to bump up your grade. Although she doesn't allow laptops or cell phones and she's super strict about them. And another downfall is she uses no powerpoint slides and just stands up there and talks and talks writing one word on the board every so often.
love this woman. super entertaining and really opens your eyes to things you didn't realize unless you are a religions student

If you keep up with the  readings and can write a half decent essay on an exam, you'll get an A+ for this course. I was freaked out at the midterm because it was only an hour long and we had to write an essay and do short answer Qs, but she's an easy marker. Do the readings, prove that you've read them in the essays and you're golden!

I found that this professor sincerely WANTED the students to do well if they were willing. She explained her definitions & every term clearly and told us all what was to be expected on the exam. Even though I use basically only my laptop in all my courses, the switch in this class was really helpful and she didn't speak too fast so you missed info.

I personally felt like SRS1110 is all hype. This class was boring and was offered at 7-10pm (WHY?). No amount of jokes, and anecdotes made it entertaining enough to stay after the break. However, the midterm and final were easy (only studied for 20 minutes before) and notes are available on notebro if you wish to skip. Choose a better elective!
awesome class. awesome prof. as long as you don't miss class and take extensive notes, you're good to go and guaranteed a true eye-opening learning experience.

Do not take any course with this professor if you care about your education. Doesn't know how to organize a course and didn't even give students any marks before the deadline to drop a course. Disgraceful and unfair to all students.

BADLY organized. No one knew how they were doing in the class until the end of November when the midterm marks were finally available, partly because the midterm was set so late - beginning of November.

Great prof, interesting lectures, provides great examples and life-experiences to help illustrate some of the material.  3 multiple-choice exmas for this class. DO NOT get caught talking in her class, or caught with any electronics!! She's all about respecting others!
Awesome prof, good class!
Awesome prof. Made things interesting, knows her stuff. Nice enough, little strict on electronics but she's not the only one. Her class was the only one I didn't skip, it was too interesting.

Avoid this class. Much rambling with random references to the odd key word. Impossible to identify possible course material from continuous ramblings. I stopped attending the class entirely and read the textbook and got a good grade - I couldn't bear the lectures.

This was by far the worst class I have had in my 3 years at Ottawa U. The teacher missed over 2/3rds of the classes and when she was in class she would present video after video. I would avoid this class and this teacher.

Very interesting. No need to read material! If you go to every class you are guaranteed an A! She presents some shocking information for dramatic effect but a lot of what she has to say is very important to learn especially for young women.

Very informative course, but one that demands the student be an active listener and note-taker. Skipping is absolutely not a good idea, because she covers a lot every class and anything might be on the tests. She's very engaging, enthusiastic, and thought-provoking. Highly recommended course.

Doesn't allow electronics in class, so you'll be spending every waking moment scrawling down notes because any given side note can be tested on.  This is partly because she tries to entertain, but then tests you on the "entertainment".  Very little of the core material is taught.  Her movies are abominations, and are also tested on.  Very unhelpful

The best and most useful part of this course was the textbook. Lectures were a jumble of disorganized "key terms", note-taking is almost impossible, and there was zero feedback/expectations for assignments. Don't take this course.

Waste of money, waste of time. often saw her napping in her car on Laurier AVE, ALWAYS late for class (hmm). Taught stereotypes and lies. Stripped abuse experiences of any sort of individuality. Exam hassporadic questions never covered. Was extremely painful to listen to her for 3 hours. She teaches her opinions and not facts. Dangerous learning.

I had her for World Religions. If she teaches the course again avoid it like the plague. She doesn't lecture, you watch an hour long movie every second class, followed by class presentations. If you want to learn something avoid class and read the textbook. If you want an easy A without learning anything however, this may be the class for you.
This was for her witchcraft course. She is an excellent teacher, very personable, and makes you really interested in the topic. Also, multipule choice exam or short answer. You get to choose!

Extremely knowledgable prof; very animated teaching style; interesting material; clear expectations; marks based on 1 mid-term and 1 final- all multiple choice- each multiple choice question being worth 1% of your final grade; textbook utilized greatly; no notes posted on web; cool movies shown; massive class size

One word to describe this prof: Epic. I was in her witchcraft class and it was hands down best class I've had. She is hilarious and so well informed. She provides great perspective on the subject matter, and it a perfectly fair marker!

Super easy class, got a really good grade. However the prof is frustrating to listen to. I'm a third year history student and tons of her historical facts are way off, or she combines certain events with others that happened 70 years in the past. If you're interested in something learned in her class, do your own research to find out the truth!

She is the best professor I had during first year university, hands down.  She is extremely knowledgeable and her lectures are always interesting.  Exams are decent - just make sure you do the readings and attend the lectures.  I would without a doubt take another class of hers in future years.
Worst prof I have ever had. Does not seem to care for well-being of students in the slightest. Will never take a class by her again.

Terrible teacher. You will fall asleep in her class. Have her for first year WS and is a huge waste of time. Wishing to have had Sethna for this class. Never will I take her class again. Very unclear, scattered and annoying to listen to and look at. Exams are multiple choice and a lot of questions are a crap shoot.

I am in her Witchcraft class and it is by far my favourite course I have ever taken.  She is a great teacher and the 3 hours absolutely flies by!  She is a very engaging speaker and really makes things interesting!
She is an incredibly engaging speaker so her lectures are always fascinating. Her exams are very straightforward and are entirely multiple choice. Her class was my favourite.

Very easy class (Witchcraft) and quite interesting. Great lecturer, not boring, speaks  loudly. VERY chill, laid back, isn't very "professorish" but is interesting. Cool stories. If you want an easy A but to also be interested in the class, then take Witchcraft. Also very outspoken, loves to swear which tends to bring some laughs.

extremely rude when replying to emails. class is ridiculously boring.. if you wanna learn about lies then go ahead.. she says she class is really easy on the first but... thats a lie. everything she says is a lie and shes a terrible prof.. extremly boring. do yourself a favour and never take witchcraft.

Really enjoy Rabinovitch as a professor. She may not be the most challenging but I looked forward to going to each class. it was just fun and she has a great character, sarcastic and ramble-y. Never a dull moment, never stale, never monotone. Not difficult, not complaining!

veryy easy class ! im suprised at the reviews, Rabinovitch is a very entertaining teacher. we watch many movies and videos. we never used the textbook, complete waste of money! come to class (many ppl tend not to & i couldn't imagine why)& give effort to the only 2 assignments and you will get an A garunteed. ps- TA's mark everything
Nice in person, rude in e-mails. A waist of time. Pointless class. You will not learn anything.

I had no idea that this class would be useless. I did not learn anything except we should all view things from a femine point of view thats it thats all. Prof is nice, loves to swear, kind of nutty. She "claims" to understand other cultures and religions. Not true. Movies are depressing. one midterm 40,and final 60. With no effort, B, study hard A.
A fantastic first year women's studies prof.  Excellent lectures.

My lowest mark this semester (A-). Took it thinking it will be easy, and it wasn't difficult, I was just not interested (At ALL) in the material. Waste of my time, money and energy. I would recommend taking something more interesting

I thought she was very disorganized on the rare occasions when she taught a lecture and did not rely on a film. The text and reader were almost entirely useless, except for maybe two questions on the take-home exam. Assignments had little to do with lectures or readings. The class was a waste of my time.
It was decent. She is entertaining, but I found her lack of explanations for assignments disconcerting. Also, I thought she swore too much.
Awesome professor. Perfect lecturer. Very entertaining, interesting, and informative class.
Very funny teacher, her classes was always extremely entertaining. Class was easy, as long as you attend it and read the material she tells you to read. I would take her class again!
The class was interesting and easy. Her story about her near death experience changed my outlook on life. I would suggest taking the class for this lecture alone.

The midterm was surprisingly difficult, however the final was fair. The guest speaker was horrible and very difficult to understand. Complete lack of clarity. Rabinovitch is quite unprofessional in her teaching. I was quite put off by this.
Best prof ever!!  Her class was so interesting, and her teaching style was really engaging and fun for the students.  As long as you listen/take notes you'll ace the 2 tests.

I took intro to female studies with this proff and it was the easiest class ever. I attended 30% of the classes, didnt buy the textbook and still ended up with a B. There were no midterms or finals just an ad critique essay, and a final take home paper. Both were easy and required no readings or notes to be taken. The proff is really nice too!!
She's so much fun to listen to

By far the EASIEST course I have ever taken. The class is a little interesting (especially the Nazi videos) but attendance is not mandatory. Her exams are 75% the same and she ask's the same Q's year after year. If you want an A+, take this class. If you cant get an A, you've failed at being a human.
Wonderful woman and professor. She was interesting, and so was the course.

I have had this prof 4 times and each time I get the exact same material. She doesn't cater to the class, she just manipulates it to fit the title. She's a brilliant woman and very nice but as far as being a good prof.. She lacks. I loved her the first time but the movies and lectures became repetitive and boring.
Awesome teacher! Really good summer class.
Rabinovitch rocks!
Interesting class, and very humorous
Teaches to her audience, knows/understands her audience. Good luck Trying to get into her class!
she was fantastic
easy class, but towards the end of the term it feels as if she's cramming alot of info into each lecture.

Shelley Rabinovitch seems like the kind of person I would like to be friends with. However, there is a difference between a good professor and a good teacher. Dr. Rabinovitch is a good professor.  I sincerely hope that the bad period she is going through in her life gets better very soon. She deserves better, and so do her students.

WITCHCRAFT Great prof. She explains things really well, and can make boring subject matter more interesting. She has relevant stories. I did not enjoy the guest lectures by Prof. Guille-something. She didnt speak loud enough for us to hear. (marion auditorium)

GREAT PROF! there is a reason why her class is the most popular on campus! she's knows her material well and doesn't hesitate to offer guidance to students and answer tough questions. I disagree with the negative comments- she's just trying to make otherwise dull material interesting to appeal to our age group...and it WORKS!
completely awesome class! she is the most entertaining prof I've had! Her lectures are informative, and she's a riot. It doesn't feel like class.

She is such a great lecturer! She is funny and really enjoys talking about her ideas.  I disagree with the negative reviews, she isn't lazy, she gets there and gets the job done effectively.  She lectures to the average age group she is teaching too, she understands it can be boring and works with that. I think she creates the ideal course for 400.
GREAT teacher. join the class, you'll see!
Great prof.  Just go to class and you'll do well.  Her lectures are interesting and well-rounded.  Such a great class -- don't miss it!
PART-TIME PROF OF THE YEAR!!!!

Great course.  Prof Rab is a great professor because she is down to earth and very easy to listen to.  Having a prof who believes in what they are teaching inspires you to learn as much as you can.  The size of the class should speak for itself.
Not a great class, too much foul language used that is not necessary. Easy prof, be there take notes, WATCH THE VIDEOS!! Most exam questions are from the videos.
she is lazy and often misses class, late with grades, shows lots of movies.
Enjoyable class, i took it during the summer and it was pretty good for a summer class.
i loved this class.. DO NOT BUY THE TEXT BOOK, just take it out of the library for the final.  class attendance is really not mandatory, but interesting.  she is a great professor.

Awesome class. This prof is a great lecturer; incorporates personal experience, hilarious She's a great story-teller. Keeps your attention for the full lecture. Multi choice mid-term and final are easy, just know your stuff. I didn't ever want to miss one of her lectures. Neomancy book = waste of money! Most popular course on campfor a reason!

Awesome class. This prof is a great lecturer; incorporates personal experience, hilarious She's a great story-teller. Keeps your attention for the full lecture. Multi choice mid-term and final are easy, just know your stuff. I didn't ever want to miss one of her lectures. Neomancy book = waste of money! Most popular course on campfor a reason!

I have no complaints for Professor Rabinovitch. I enjoy her sense of humour, but for students who don't have one it could be frustrating I guess... I found that her way of teaching allowed me to retain more material than any other class I've taken in University.

Very nice woman.  She does not take herself too seriously and she laughs alot which makes class fun.  She thinks outside the box so it is interesting just to hear her ideas during lectures.  She has a wacky anecdote or personal experience for every topic so it is really entertaining.

This was the worst class I could have imagined. She was never prepared for class.  We learned NOTHING. She used movies instead of teaching anything herself.  She tells the class far too much about her personal life and seems to make her lectures up as she goes along.  Her good ideas are lost in poor orgaization and bad lectures.

Complete waste of time, she didn't even seem to want to show up. I swear only two classes out of the entire semester did she show up on time - the rest were often 10-15 minutes late. Boring material, sluggish lectures, sorry attempts to be funny that often got sidetracked, etc. Easy class but far from enjoyable or worthwhile.

This prof turned women's studies into a sewing circle.  She strives to identify with every marginalized group in society.  All to often, the class takes over the discussion, and pointless personal anecdotes are offered.  This may as well be Armchair Pyschology 1100. But she must be right, 'cause she was a member of the media for so long.
The most interesting class Ive ever taken. Very easy and lectures are really entertaining!

i DUNNO ABOUT THIS ONE.  YOU MUST ATTEND ALL LECTURES AND FILMS AND READ THE MATERIAL TO DO WELL. MULTIPLE CHOICE EXAMS BUT TRICKY. I JUST FIND THE CLASS A BIT ONE SIDED ON THE SUBJECT OF PAGANISM CAUSE SHE IS ONE, SHE MAKES IT SOUND NORMAL, QUITE STRANGE TO ME BUT OVERALL SHE'S COOL
Awesome teacher!  Great sense of humour,which helps in the learning process.
Overrated class. Very boring and this woman has no concept of how to teach a course.

Nice person but her lectures are hard to follow. She is all over the place and doesn't have any visual notes. You have to guess what is important and that is really hard when she goes off on tangents every 5 seconds from someone's question. Very frustrating.

This class was such a joke. All everyone did was talk the whole class. You don't even need to go, considering your mark is based on 3 essays. You also don't need the textbook, because the essays have nothing to do with the text. Boring and ridiculously easy class.
Great Class. Movies + Guest Speakers. Reading was simple, not much reading in a week. 2 mid'term essays + 1 final take home essay. Automatic 10%. Good if you need an easy elective.
Great course, really interesting. Lots of discussion (take it if you like to talk). Easy readings, mostly essays and an essay take-home. It was good.
don't know what all the hype is about, I was bored senseless and sick of the notes, disappointing course material and a complete drag going to lectures.

An awesome course; her lectures flow smoothly, so its easy to pay attention and take notes. She also mixes personal anecdotes with the material making the course even more interesting and relaxed. No assingments, just a midterm and final; both are multiple choice and she always mentions during the lectures what exactly you need to know.
I love this class, we do take an awful lot of notes, but we get to watch movies aswell. She is very helpful and is a lot of fun!

2 thumbs up! Definitely a great course with an even greater prof... no way u can fall asleep in her class!
best calss i ever took. interseting, clear, facinationg, gret text and reading choices. easy tests.

Interesting and VERY easy class! So far, the mid-term was a breaze. Sometimes though, she does get off topic and half way through her stories you think "what the hell is she talking about??" Good class otherwise!

Absolutely fantastic class.  Sitting through her lectures are a breeze - because she makes them so interesting!  Easy multiple choice midterm and exam. Gave us bonus marks for dressing up at Halloween.  This class is in high demand - but definitely try to get in!
She's THE BEST. Her class has got to be the most fun on campus.
